<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Prepare a Strategic Plan for a School</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1001" relname="joint">Developing a strategic plan for a school begins with the alignment of the district strategic plan .</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1001" relname="joint">For example , one of the goals in the district strategic plan may be to improve student attendance .</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1001" relname="joint">Taking that goal for the school may be to improve school attendance by 2 percent over 2 years .</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1005" relname="span">Usually , strategic plans are for a five year period ,</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="5" relname="elaboration">so the goals can reflect that as well .</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1009" relname="span">Each goal</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="7" relname="elaboration">that is selected for the school 's strategic plan</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1008" relname="same_unit">must align with the district 's strategic plan .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1012" relname="span">The school may have fewer goals</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="10" relname="elaboration">( usually no more than three can be reached in one year ) ,</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1013" relname="span">and each goal should have activities</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1014" relname="span">to support the goal as well as a budget</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="13" relname="purpose">to support the activities .</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1017" relname="span">Each goal must be developed in a " shared experience " with all stakeholders</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="15" relname="elaboration">( teachers , parents , students if high school , and staff ) .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="span">Listed in a step by step method is the process</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1019" relname="span">one would use</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="18" relname="purpose">to develop one of the goals in the strategic plan .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1020" relname="sequence">After each goal activity is completed ,</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1021" relname="span">then the information is compiled into a comprehensive strategic plan for the school year</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1022" relname="span">which includes a spending plan</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="22" relname="elaboration">that is aligned to the school 's total budget .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1025" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1025" relname="sequence">Determine current percent of attendance .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1026" relname="joint">Most elementary schools are around 95 % attendance with middle schools around 92 % ,</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1026" relname="joint">and high schools around 90 % .</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1029" relname="span">Each school is provided a report of attendance</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="28" relname="elaboration">reporting on a monthly basis by the District Office .</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1028" relname="sequence">Discuss with stakeholders the current attendance rate and the need for improvement .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1032" relname="span">Discuss a 1 % increase per year for the next two years ,</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="31" relname="elaboration">which is aligned to the District goal .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1028" relname="sequence">Provide stakeholders with historic attendance reporting</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1028" relname="sequence">and indicate which months are " problematic " .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1036" relname="span">Provide stakeholders with number of students</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1037" relname="span">needed</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="36" relname="purpose">to make a 1 % increase .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1039" relname="span">Develop with stakeholders activities</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="38" relname="purpose">to meet the attendance goal of improvement by 1 % .</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1042" relname="span">Examples of possible activities include monthly award assemblies for perfect attendance</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="40" relname="elaboration">( usually elementary school students ) ,</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1044" relname="span">privilege certificates</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1045" relname="same_unit">( such as no homework for a day )</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1046" relname="span">for middle and high school students , attendance clerk</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="44" relname="purpose">to monitor student attendance ,</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1048" relname="preparation">and make friendly home phone calls daily for absent students ,</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1048" relname="span">Vice Principal or other administrator may make home visits for students</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1049" relname="span">who have missed 3 days or more before December</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1050" relname="same_unit">to determine</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="51" relname="condition">if any interventions may be appropriate ,</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1051" relname="span">and end-of-year trips may be tied to attendance .</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1053" relname="span">These are just a few activities</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="52" relname="elaboration">that schools use .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1052" relname="sequence">Be sure to discuss them thoroughly with all stakeholders .</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1052" relname="sequence">Determine the cost of each activity</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1052" relname="sequence">and add this into the school 's budget .</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1057" relname="joint">Additional personnel costs may need to be approved by the district budgeting department .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1058" relname="sequence">Share the final comprehensive goal with all stakeholders in a variety of venues .</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1060" relname="joint">For parents and community , include the goal on the school 's website</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1060" relname="joint">and show the results as well as activities .</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="62" relname="condition">If there is a monthly newsletter ,</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1062" relname="span">share the goal and activities in the newsletter .</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1065" relname="span">Send positive notes to students</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="63" relname="elaboration">who have improved upon their attendance ,</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1066" relname="span">and make personal telephone calls to families ,</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="65" relname="elaboration">thanking them for their child 's improved attendance .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1067" relname="joint">During back-to-school night activities , be sure to have teaching staff discuss the importance of good attendance to student learning ,</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1068" relname="span">and provide handouts to parents</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1070" relname="span">discussing the goal , the activities</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="69" relname="purpose">to reach the goal , the budget , and scientific research</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1069" relname="same_unit">supporting good school attendance .</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1073" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1074" relname="span">Always include all stakeholders in the process</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="73" relname="elaboration">of developing the strategic plan .</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1073" relname="joint">Keep the planning process to a manageable level .</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1077" relname="span">Stakeholders will be unable to attend many of the meetings .</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="76" relname="elaboration">Administrators must do their homework .</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1078" relname="span">Be sure to get all the data together</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="78" relname="circumstance">before beginning the process .</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1080" relname="preparation">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1080" relname="joint">Remember that there will always be folks against the process .</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="1080" relname="joint">Keep a positive attitude .</segment>
<segment id="83" parent="1080" relname="joint">Go back to the research on attendance and its importance in learning .</segment>
<segment id="84" parent="1080" relname="joint">Educate your teachers in the planning process .</segment>
<segment id="85" parent="1084" relname="span">They will be your most positive supporters</segment>
<segment id="86" parent="85" relname="condition">if they are engaged from the very beginning .</segment>
